Ram Wertheim was named to the newly created post of senior vice president and general counsel of Capital Markets Assurance Corp., a subsidiary of this banking and financial services company.
Mr. Wertheim had been an associate at the New York law firm of Simpson Thacher & Bartlett.
Capital Markets is a provider of financial guarantees for corporate debt, particularly asset-backed securitization.
The face value of debt outstanding that the unit has guaranteed, as of August, was $2.57 billion, up from $1.28 billion a year earlier. 

